 and merge them?\n\nThe tube geometry twists -- that is what the Frenet Frames are all about. I am not sure how one would know how to orient the `CircleGeometry` at the far end so that the vertices would line up with the tube vertices.\n\nOn a unrelated note, the tube and end-cap faces should have a different material index. This way, the `repeat` can be controlled independently.\n","created_at":"2014-06-17T16:00:37.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/4933#issuecomment-46327409","id":46327409,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4933","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ2MzI3NDA5","updated_at":"2014-06-17T16:00:37.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/46327409","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"> The tube geometry twists -- that is what the Frenet Frames are all about. I am not sure how one would know how to orient the `CircleGeometry` at the far end so tha